                <head>485. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The United States ratified the Convention on the Territorial Sea and the
                    Contiguous Zone (15 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 1606), the Convention on
                    the High Seas (13 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 2312), the Convention on
                    Fishing and Conservation of the Living Resources of the High Seas (17 <gloss
                        target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 138), and the Convention on the Continental
                    Shelf (15 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 471) on March 24, 1961. All four
                    conventions had been signed by the United States on September 15, 1958, and had
                    received the advice and consent of the Senate on May 26, 1960. The United States
                    deposited its ratifications with the Secretary-General of the United Nations on
                    April 12, 1961.</p>
            </div>
